<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8479> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8479" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 732, footnote 67" ;
	dprr:hasID 8479 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7149> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7149" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 180. Leg., lieut. 191. See MRR 1.355. Münzer (no. 46) suggests that Livy 36.12.9 should be emended to read either ab A. Postumio legato, qui ab Atilio Cephallaniae praepositus fuerat or, with Perizonius, qui ab Atilio legatus Cephallaniae praepositus fuerat. He should be listed as above. Leg., amb. 175. See MRR 1.403. This embassy must have left Italy for Macedonia in the spring or early summer of 176 and, while some members of it visited the Bastarni, returned to Rome in 175 (P. Meloni, Perseo 82 and note 3, 83, 85 and notes 2 and 3; see also Walbank, Comm. Polyb. 3.281-283). Censor, 174. In MRR 1.404, refer also to Liv. 45.17.1." ;
	dprr:hasID 7149 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2795> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2795" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with instructions from the Senate to assist Paullus in organizing Macedonia (Liv. 45.17.2-3, and 29-31). Claudius and Domitius went to Achaea to summon the Achaean leaders to Rome in person (Liv. 45.31.9-11; cf. Polyb. 30.13.8-11), and Fabius went to Lesbos to destroy Antissa and incorporate it with Methymna (Liv. 45.31.14)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2795 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2752> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2752" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Selected by Paullus to negotiate the surrender of Perseus in Samothrace (Liv. 45.4.7). On the Postumii, see Lübker nos. 3 and 4." ;
	dprr:hasID 2752 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2655> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2655" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Crete to secure additional auxiliary troops for Licinius' army (Liv. 42.35.7). On Postumius, see Münzer, APF 213ff.; Lübker no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2655 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2608> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2608" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A. Postumius Albinus (Luscus) succeeded L. Cornelius Lentulus. Liv. 42.10.6. On Lentulus, see 213, note 8; on Postumius, Münzer, Bull. Com., 67 (1939) 27-30; Lübker, no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2608 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2557> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2557" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Verr. 2.1.106; Liv. 41.27.1; 43.16.2; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 123, 458f.; Vell. 1.10.6; Plin. NH 7.157; Fest. 360 L; and on Fulvius, Val. Max. 2.7.5. They expelled nine from the Senate including a brother of Fulvius the Censor (see 180, note 3; Liv. 41.27.2; Val. Max. 2.7.5; Vell. 1.10.6; Frontin. Str. 4.1.32), and degraded many knights. They carried on an extensive program of building in Rome, Fulvius also in Pisaurum, Fundi, Potentia, and Sinuessa (Liv. 41.27.1-2, and 5-13). Fulvius also robbed the temple of Juno Lacinia of its marble tiles for his temple of Fortuna Equestris, but was compelled to return them (Liv. 42.3.1-11; Val. Max. 1.1.20). He dedicated his temple in 173 (Liv. 42.10.5) and Postumius founded the lustrum (42.10.1-4). They chose M. Aemilius Lepidus Princeps Senatus (Liv. 41.27.1). On Postumius, see 180, Consuls; Münzer, APF 213; Lübker no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2557 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2555> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2555" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Identified by Münzer (Bull. Com. 67 [1939] 27-30) with the duovir named in an inscription from the Largo Argentina (Ann. Epig. 1935, p. 228, no. 88, from Bull. Com. 61 [1933] 163ff., CIL 1(2) 2.2711) and with the one named on the altar to Verminus (ILS 4019). On the pestilence to men and cattle which occasioned the altar, see Obseq. 10; and Livy 41. 21.5-7. See Münzer, APF 213; Lübker no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2555 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2554> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2554" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See most recently Marchetti-Longhi, Bull. Com. 71 (1943-45) 58f.; and Degrassi, Doxa 2 (1949) 67f." ;
	dprr:hasID 2554 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2553> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2553" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent with several other senators to Macedonia to investigate Dardanian complaints regarding an understanding between Perseus and the Bastarnae (Polyb. 25.6.5-6). They reported the war in Dardania (Liv. 41.19.4; cf. App. Mac. 11.1)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2553 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2440> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2440" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 40.35.1; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 122, 456f.; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Luscus' cognomen, Liv. 45.17.2; Fest. 360 L. Both Consuls were assigned the province of Liguria (Liv. 40.35.8, and 36.6; and on Postumius, 40.41.1-2 and 5-9). Calpurnius died early in the year (Liv. 40.37.1). On Postumius, see Lübker no. 6; Münzer, Bull. Com. 67 (1939) 27-30." ;
	dprr:hasID 2440 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2320> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2320" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Lübker no. 3; Münzer, APF 213ff." ;
	dprr:hasID 2320 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2317> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2317" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elections: Liv. 39.23.2 Provinces omitted in Livy." ;
	dprr:hasID 2317 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2296> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2296" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 39.7.8-9. On Postumius, see Lübker no. 3." ;
	dprr:hasID 2296 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2192> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2192" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Placed in command of Cephallenia by Atilius (Liv. 36.12.9)." ;
	dprr:hasID 2192 .
